Chaohong Wang was born on 16 July 1996 in Poyang, China. He received his Bachelor's degree in applied physics from the Huaqiao University in 2018. He then pursued a Master's degree in condensed matter physics at Xiamen University. During his Master's, he worked on the ice uncleation using Molecular Dynamics simulations. He is currently a PhD student at the Utrecht University, where he studies the self-assembly of zeolites with coarsed-grained model.